meanings.definition: To have moved in a zigzag pattern.
meanings.sent1: The squirrel tictacked across the yard to avoid the cat.
meanings.sent2: She tictacked through the crowded market to reach the other side.
meanings.sent3: The puppy tictacked around the room, chasing its tail in circles.
meanings.sent4: The kite tictacked in the sky, dancing with the wind.
meanings.sent5: The river tictacked through the valley, carving a winding path.

meanings.definition: To have attached or affixed something in a zigzag pattern.
meanings.sent1: He tictacked the photos on the wall in a diagonal line.
meanings.sent2: She tictacked the ribbon onto the gift box with care.
meanings.sent3: The child tictacked the stickers on the paper, creating a colorful design.
meanings.sent4: The carpenter tictacked the trim along the edge of the door, ensuring a snug fit.
meanings.sent5: The gardener tictacked the vines to the trellis, guiding their growth upward.
